s.text: What is largely Alexander's doing, however, is that the remaining grants reflect not a serious commitment to high culture in America but a kind of passive, middlebrow populism.
The NEA does still support some elitist high culture, including the Metropolitan Museum and the Seattle Opera.
Until the budget cuts, the NEA gave awards in 17 categories corresponding to familiar disciplines in the fine arts.
The strategy has worked, and may have been necessary, and of course it's easy to carp from the outside.
